    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-16T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="480"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560AL/6–1647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Troutman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-16T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 16, 1947—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>509. Personal for Clayton from Wilcox. 1. Am being asked what is status of new
                    program for aid to Europe, whether it will be presented to <gloss
                        target="#t_ECE1">ECE</gloss> meeting and how it is related to tariff and
                        <gloss target="#t_ITO1">ITO</gloss> negotiations.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d480fn1">For documentation regarding the United States interest in
                        the rehabilitation of Europe and the “Marshall Plan,” see <ref
                            target="frus1947v03#pg_197">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, pp.
                            197</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. Contrast Bevin’s speech June 13 praising US offer of further aid with Cripps’
                    speech June 6<note n="2" xml:id="d480fn2">The speech was given on June 11; see
                        footnote 4, above.</note> bitterly criticizing US and disparaging importance
                    tariff negotiations and <gloss target="#t_ITO1">ITO</gloss>. Inference that aid
                    program makes results Geneva negotiations unimportant tends to impair our
                    bargaining position here. Question for consideration is how we can use program
                    to improve bargaining position.</p>
                <p>3. Assumption here has been that you will not return until wool issue settled. On
                    basis reports in press, am now being asked when you will return Geneva, whether
                    you will stop in London and Paris en route and what is schedule for subsequent
                    trips. [Wilcox.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Troutman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
